    <statement><p>Determine the inverses of the following functions.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>f(x)=\sqrt[3]{2x-1}</m></p>
<p><m>f^{-1}(x)=</m> <fillin characters="30" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>g(x)=3\ln(-4x)+1</m></p>
<p><m>g^{-1}(x)=</m> <fillin characters="30" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>h(x)=5^{x^3}</m></p>
<p><m>h^{-1}(x)=</m> <fillin characters="30" name="AnSwEr0003"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>r(x)=\frac{1}{x}</m></p>
<p><m>r^{-1}(x)=</m> <fillin characters="30" name="AnSwEr0004"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x^{3}+1}{2}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{-\exp\mathopen{}\left(\frac{x-1}{3}\right)}{4}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(\frac{\ln\mathopen{}\left(x\right)}{1.60944}\right)^{0.333333}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{x}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The inverse functions are:</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><nbsp/></p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
                                            y \amp  = \sqrt[3]{2x-1}\\
                                            y^3 \amp  = 2x-1\\
                                            y^3 + 1 \amp  = 2x\\
                                            \frac{1}{2}y^3 + \frac{1}{2} \amp  x\\
                                            y \amp  = \frac{1}{2}x^3 + \frac{1}{2} \text{ (swap variables)}\\
                                            f^{-1} \amp  = \frac{1}{2}x^3 + \frac{1}{2}
                                        \end{aligned}</me></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><nbsp/></p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
                                            y \amp  = 3ln(-4x)+1\\
                                            y-1 \amp  = 3\ln(-4x)\\
                                            \frac{1}{3}y-\frac{1}{3} \amp  = \ln(-4x)\\
                                            e^{\frac{1}{3}y - \frac{1}{3}} \amp  -4x\\
                                            -\frac{1}{4}e^{\frac{1}{3}y - \frac{1}{3}} \amp  = x\\
                                            y \amp  = -\frac{1}{4}e^{\frac{1}{3}x - \frac{1}{3}} \text{ (swap variables)}\\
                                            g^{-1}(x) \amp  = -\frac{1}{4}e^{\frac{1}{3}x - \frac{1}{3}}
                                        \end{aligned}</me></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><nbsp/></p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
                                            y \amp  = 5^{x^3}\\
                                            \ln(y) \amp  = \ln\left(5^{x^3}\right) = \ln(5)x^3\\
                                            \frac{\ln(y)}{\ln(5)} \amp  = x^3\\
                                            \sqrt[3]{\frac{\ln(y)}{\ln(5)}} \amp  = x\\
                                            y \amp  = \sqrt[3]{\frac{\ln(x)}{\ln(5)}} \text{ (swap variables)}\\
                                            h^{-1}(x) \amp  = \sqrt[3]{\frac{\ln(x)}{\ln(5)}}
                                        \end{aligned}</me></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><nbsp/></p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
                                            y \amp  = \frac{1}{x}\\
                                            \frac{1}{y} \amp  = x\\
                                            y \amp  = \frac{1}{x} \text{ (swap variables)}\\
                                            r^{-1}(x) \amp  = \frac{1}{x}
                                        \end{aligned}</me></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</solution>
